Initial inference on the data¶

  • There are total of 300698 rows/records on the data
  • There are 53 features
  • Out of 53 features 33 features has null values
  • Date values are not imported in proper format
  • Few of the features seems to have no useful data and we can actually drop those
  • We have data starting from 29th Mar'15 till the end of the year

# Let's visualise Counts of Service request over City in Bar plot
plt.figure(figsize=(20,10))
ys=df_Customer_service_req['City'].value_counts()
xs = np.arange(0,len(df_Customer_service_req['City'].unique()),1)
ys.plot.bar()
for x,y in zip(xs,ys.to_numpy()):
    label = y
    plt.annotate(label,(x,y+2500),rotation=90,textcoords="offset points",xytext=(0,10),verticalalignment='center')
plt.title("Counts of Service request over City",loc="center", fontdict= {'family': 'serif',
        'color':  'darkred',
        'weight': 'normal',
        'size': 16})
plt.xlabel("Name of the city",fontdict= {'family': 'serif',
        'color':  'darkred',
        'weight': 'normal',
        'size': 16})
plt.ylabel("Counts of Service request",fontdict= {'family': 'serif',
        'color':  'darkred',
        'weight': 'normal',
        'size': 16})
plt.ylim(0,(1.1*(max(ys))))

Statistical test¶

1. Whether the average response time across complaint types is similar or not (overall)¶

  • Since the test is all about comparing the averages across the group ANNOVA (Analysis of Variance) test is used
  • We have one independent variable Resolution time between the groups and so One way ANNOVA would be used

Null Hypotheses¶

  • The average response time across the complaint types are equal
  • Ho: μ1=μ2=..=μn

Alternage Hypotheses¶

  • The average response time across the complaint types are not equal
  • H1: All μ are not equal
Test steps:¶
  • We will determine the pvalue for the groups
  • If the P value is less than alpha (0.05) we will reject null hypotheses
  • If the P value is greater than alpha (0.05) we will accept the null hypotheses

In [89]:
if (pval<0.05):
    print('Null hypothesis is rejected since p value ({}) is less than 0.05'.format(np.around(pval,decimals=2)))
else:
    print('Null hypothesis is accepted since p value ({}) is greater than 0.05'.format(np.around(pval,decimals=2)))

Null hypothesis is rejected since p value (0.0) is less than 0.05

Interpretation from the P value¶

  • The p-value obtained from the Oneway ANNOVA is ~0.0 which is less than 0.05(alpha)
  • With which we can determine with 95% confidence that the average resolution time of the different types of complaints are not same
  • We have rejected the null hypothesis

-------The average resolution time for the different type of compliants are not the same------¶

2. Are the type of complaints or service requested and location related?¶

  • Identify the features that has type of complaints and location related details
  • Since the relationship between variables are supposed to be indentified we need to perform the Statistical test related to the correlation
  • Chi square test can be done for this case to test the relationship between multiple variables

Null Hypothesis¶

  • Ho: There is no is that no relationship exists between the Service request type and location

Alternate Hypothesis¶

  • H1 : There is significant relationship between the Service request type and location

Null hypothesis is rejected since p value (0.0) is less than 0.05

Interpretation from the P value¶

  • The p-value obtained from the chi square test is ~0.0 which is less than 0.05(alpha)
  • With which we can determine with 95% confidence that there is a significant relationship between the variables
  • We have rejected the null hypothesis
